{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Adrian Beria Blog","author":"Adrian Beria"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"dd12398b-d7e5-5ad7-84ce-042bd61b8006","excerpt":"Introduction Redux Thunk middleware allows you to write action creators that return a function instead of an action. The thunk can be used…","html":"<h2>Introduction</h2>\n<p>Redux Thunk middleware allows you to write action creators that return a function instead of an action. The thunk can be used to delay the dispatch of an action, or to dispatch only if a certain condition is met. The inner function receives the store methods dispatch and getState as parameters.</p>\n<h2>What is a middleware</h2>\n<p>The middleware sits in between the dispatch and reducers, which means we can alter our dispatched actions before they get to the reducers or execute some code during the dispatch.</p>\n<h2>When to use</h2>\n<p>When we need to do any kind of asynchronous logic, we generally pair it with axios, which is a library for making HTTP requests. One of my favorite reasons to use axios over ES6 fetch is that with axios you don’t have to do convert the data you obtained from your request usding .json(), axios does this automatically, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">fetch(url).then(response =&gt; response.json()).then(data =&gt; console.log(data))\n\naxios.get(url).then(response =&gt; console.log(response))</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Installing dependencies</h2>\n<p>For an alredy created project:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">yarn add redux react-redux</code></pre></div>\n<p>If you’re doing some async</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">yarn add axios redux-thunk</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Project structure</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>src</p>\n<ul>\n<li>actions</li>\n<li>api</li>\n<li>components</li>\n<li>pages</li>\n<li>reducers</li>\n<li>store</li>\n<li>types</li>\n<li>App.js</li>\n<li>index.js</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each folder will have an index.js file inside.</p>\n<h2>Types</h2>\n<p>Inside the types folder we add our constants</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/ff67a/redux-thunk-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 544px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 21.507352941176467%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/ff67a/redux-thunk-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/c2e61/redux-thunk-1.png 148w,\n/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/08c14/redux-thunk-1.png 295w,\n/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/ff67a/redux-thunk-1.png 544w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 544px) 100vw, 544px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Actions</h2>\n<p>Inside the actions folder we add our actions creator, importing the constants we made.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/3edcd/redux-thunk-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 20.802919708029197%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/fb8a0/redux-thunk-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/1a291/redux-thunk-2.png 148w,\n/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/2bc4a/redux-thunk-2.png 295w,\n/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/fb8a0/redux-thunk-2.png 590w,\n/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/3edcd/redux-thunk-2.png 822w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>API</h2>\n<p>This is where we will use axios, we will do all our requests on these folders and it will look like this.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4bd9a9748cfd2fe5ee4a3328388b0ec0/13ec1/redux-thunk-3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 13.6226034308779%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4bd9a9748cfd2fe5ee4a3328388b0ec0/fb8a0/redux-thunk-3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4bd9a9748cfd2fe5ee4a3328388b0ec0/1a291/redux-thunk-3.png 148w,\n/static/4bd9a9748cfd2fe5ee4a3328388b0ec0/2bc4a/redux-thunk-3.png 295w,\n/static/4bd9a9748cfd2fe5ee4a3328388b0ec0/fb8a0/redux-thunk-3.png 590w,\n/static/4bd9a9748cfd2fe5ee4a3328388b0ec0/526de/redux-thunk-3.png 885w,\n/static/4bd9a9748cfd2fe5ee4a3328388b0ec0/13ec1/redux-thunk-3.png 991w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>We learned about Redux principles in very few texts, but to truly grasp it we need to create a project, we’re actually gonna do two, one will be a small project where we will use all the concepts we learned today and for async we will use Redux Thunk. For the other project we will use Redux Saga, Selectors and Models, all of these concepts we will learn them in another post before doing said project.</p>\n<p>See you on the next post.</p>\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\n<p><strong>Eng Adrian Beria.</strong></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Redux Thunk","date":"February 20, 2020"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/10-redux-thunk/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/16-third-project-redux-part-2/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Third Project - Redux - Part 2 Searchbar and Modal"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/9-setting-redux/"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}}}}